# JRXML to Thymeleaf Template Conversion Rules

When asked to convert legacy JasperReports (JRXML) to HTML/Thymeleaf templates:

1. UNIFORM TYPOGRAPHY: The entire document must use a single, uniform font-family (e.g., font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;).
2. PRESERVE LAYOUT INTENT: Map absolute coordinate elements (x, y, width, height) into flexible row/column layouts using CSS Flexbox or Grid. Do NOT use absolute positioning.
3. TEXT TRUNCATION: When text elements have truncation properties (e.g., net.sf.jasperreports.text.truncate.suffix="..."), apply this exact CSS pattern to the generated class:
```css
   width: [Insert width from JRXML]px;
   min-width: [Insert width from JRXML]px;
   white-space: nowrap;
   overflow: hidden;
   text-overflow: ellipsis;
